comments: Bridges (CHA) and Dinwiddie (WAS) come together at the same spot and incidental leg to leg contact occurs during rebounding.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Dinwiddie (WAS) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to Charlotte.
Bridges (CHA) establishes himself in a screening position in Caldwell-Pope's (WAS) path and absorbs the contact.
Beal (WAS) brushes Ball's (CHA) midsection and marginal contact occurs after Ball picks up his dribble.
Ball (CHA) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes two steps before releasing the pass.
Harrell (WAS) and Bridges (CHA) come together at the same spot after the release of the shot attempt and marginal body contact occurs prior to Harrell retrieving the rebound.
Bridges (CHA) makes clean contact with the ball prior to any incidental contact with Harrell's (WAS) arm.
Bridges (CHA) brushes Harrell's (WAS) right leg and marginal contact occurs during Harrell's upward shooting motion.
Kuzma (WAS) and Hayward (CHA) briefly engage and disengage as they move up the lane line.
Beal (WAS) and Hayward (CHA) engage and disengage with one another as Hayward sets the pick.
Bridges (CHA) gathers the ball with his right foot on the floor and takes two steps before starting his upward shooting motion.
Hayward (CHA) and Beal (WAS) engage and disengage with one another along the perimeter.
Beal (WAS) is already in Martin's (CHA) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Bridges (CHA) is already in Caldwell-Pope's (WAS) path and marginal contact occurs as Bridges releases from the contact.
Caldwell-Pope (WAS) has his left hand rested on Bridges' (CHA) right hip and marginal contact occurs as Bridges attempts to finish at the rim.

Ball (CHA) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Harrell (WAS) after Harrell gains possession. The shot clock correctly resets to :24 once Charlotte gains control of the ball due to Harrell establishing full control prior to the dislodge.
Caldwell-Pope (WAS) jumps to the side of Rozier (CHA) and legally contests the jump shot attempt.
Rozier (CHA) and Kuzma (WAS) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Martin (CHA) and Harrell (WAS) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Kuzma (WAS) does not abnormally or overtly extend his leg into Rozier (CHA) as Rozier legally contests the jump shot.
Martin (CHA) and Harrell (WAS) come together at the same spot and incidental contact occurs during rebounding.
Dinwiddie (WAS) commits a take foul on Ball (CHA).
Caldwell-Pope (WAS) commits a take foul on Ball (CHA).
